    x = xp + learning_rate * K @ y
    return xp, P, y, S, K, x
```

### Implementation 7: Batch Normalization on State Vector

```python
def predict(x, F, P, Q, z, R):
    xp = F @ x
    y = z - xp
    S = Q + R
    eps = 1e-8
    batch_mean = np.mean(xp, axis=0)
    batch_var = np.var(xp, axis=0)
    xn = (xp - batch_mean) / (np.sqrt(batch_var + eps))
    K = 0.5 * np.eye(x.shape[0])
    x = xn + K @ y
    return xp, P, y, S, K, x
```

